article.headline: IUPUI 64, Centenary 56
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Chris Kenny scored 12 points and Tyler Azzarelli added 11 to lead Monmouth to a 56-55 win over Central Connecticut on Friday. Monmouth (14-12, 13-4 Northeast) made a season-high 12 3-pointers and remained in a tie for first place in the conference with Fairleigh Dickinson. DeMario Anderson missed a three-pointer at the final buzzer for Central (11-15, 7-10). Rich Pittman had 15 points and Tristan Blackwood added 11 for the Blue Devils. Azzarelli had three of Monmouth's six first-half 3-pointers to give Hawks a 28-22 lead at the break. Monmouth extended the lead to 39-30 early in the second half but the Blue Devils pulled ahead with a 15-2 run. Pittman had seven points in the spurt and Central Connecticut led 45-41 midway through the period. The Hawks rallied and regains the lead at 56-52 when Dejan Delic made one of two free throws with 1:01 left. Anderson hit a three to bring Central within one point of the lead. And the Blue Devils had the ball for the final 30.4 seconds, but Anderson's miss from the left wing preserved the Hawks' victory.
